Reasoning: The paper discusses adapting techniques from database theory to optimize Answer Set Programming systems, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of the Magic Set method and Dynamic Magic Set in ASP also involves database concepts, which could place the paper in the category of Databases (cs.DB). The paper also deals with the complexity of determining whether a program is super-coherent, which involves logical reasoning and could be classified under Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Additionally, the hardness proofs involve reductions and instantiations, which could be related to Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
